{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-06-15T14:53:51.688Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command__run_shell_command_1781535231684_0","parameters":{"command":"cat > papers/README.md << 'EOF'\n# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. [ProbAct: A Probabilistic Activation Function for Deep Neural Networks](1905.10761_ProbAct_Probabilistic_Activation_Function.pdf)\n   - Authors: Kumar Shridhar, Joonho Lee, Hideaki Hayashi, et al.\n   - Year: 2019\n   - arXiv: 1905.10761\n   - Why relevant: Introduces stochastic activation by sampling from a Gaussian distribution centered at the activation mean.\n\n2. [Flex-Act: Why Learn when you can Pick?](2601.06441_FlexAct_Why_Learn_When_You_Can_Pick.pdf)\n   - Authors: Ramnath Kumar, Kyle Ritscher, Junmin Judy, Lawrence Liu, Cho-Jui Hsieh.\n   - Year: 2026\n   - arXiv: 2601.06441\n   - Why relevant: Uses Gumbel-Softmax to dynamically select (sample) the best activation function from a basis set.\n\n3. [Noisy Activation Functions](1603.00391_Noisy_Activation_Functions.pdf)\n   - Authors: Caglar Gulcehre, Marcin Moczulski, Misha Denil, Yoshua Bengio.\n   - Year: 2016\n   - arXiv: 1603.00391\n   - Why relevant: Injects noise into the saturated regime of activation functions to improve gradient flow.\n\n4. [Randomized Automatic Differentiation](2007.10412_Randomized_Automatic_Differentiation.pdf)\n   - Authors: Deniz Oktay, Nick McGreivy, Joshua Aduol, Alex Beatson, Ryan P. Adams.\n   - Year: 2020\n   - arXiv: 2007.10412\n   - Why relevant: Proposes unbiased gradient estimates through randomized path sampling in the computational graph.\n\n5. [Weight Uncertainty in Neural Networks](1505.05424_Weight_Uncertainty_Neural_Networks.pdf)\n   - Authors: Charles Blundell, Julien Cornebise, Koray Kavukcuoglu, Daan Wierstra.\n   - Year: 2015\n   - arXiv: 1505.05424\n   - Why relevant: \"Bayes by Backprop\" - treats weights as distributions and samples them, providing a framework for stochasticity in NNs.\n\n6. [Auto-Encoding Variational Bayes](1312.6114_VAE_Original_Paper.pdf)\n   - Authors: Diederik P Kingma, Max Welling.\n   - Year: 2013\n   - arXiv: 1312.6114\n   - Why relevant: Foundation of stochastic latent representations (reparameterization trick).\nEOF\n","description":"Create papers/README.md."}}
